            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The Ollama model (`Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Ollama.pm`) provides a Perl interface to the Ollama LLM (Large Language Model) API for local and remote interactions with language models. It handles HTTP communication with Ollama servers, streaming responses, structured data parsing, and comprehensive error handling.</p>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>File Location:</strong> `Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Ollama.pm` (1,758 lines)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Type:</strong> Catalyst Model (extends Catalyst::Model)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Dependencies:</strong> LWP::UserAgent, HTTP::Request, JSON, Try::Tiny, Comserv::Util::Logging</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #4CAF50; margin: 10px 0;">
                <strong>📝 Recent Updates (v1.00 - Jan 10, 2026):</strong>
                <ul style="margin: 5px 0 0 20px; font-size: 0.9em;">
                    <li><strong>Commit 7ab6174e:</strong> Critical fix for Ollama communication - restored JSON body parsing with fallback to form parameters</li>
                    <li><strong>Commit e3f58859:</strong> Improve JSON body reading in AI controller endpoint with priority-based method fallback</li>
                    <li><strong>Server Management:</strong> Docker/Podman runtime detection, systemctl integration for server lifecycle management</li>
                    <li><strong>Streaming Support:</strong> Multi-line response streaming with proper parsing for chat interactions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PREREQUISITES & KEY FEATURES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 id="prerequisites" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Ollama Server:</strong> Local (localhost:11434) or remote (e.g., 192.168.1.199:11434)</li>
                <li><strong>Network Access:</strong> HTTP connectivity to Ollama API endpoint</li>
                <li><strong>Perl Modules:</strong> LWP::UserAgent, JSON, Try::Tiny</li>
                <li><strong>Model Installed:</strong> At least one LLM model pulled (e.g., llama3.1, mistral)</li>
                <li><strong>Container Runtime:</strong> Docker or Podman (optional, for server management)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 id="features" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Key Features</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Query & Chat:</strong> Single-turn and multi-turn LLM interactions with streaming support</li>
                <li><strong>Model Management:</strong> List, pull, and remove Ollama models programmatically</li>
                <li><strong>Flexible Endpoints:</strong> Local, remote, or explicit endpoint configuration</li>
                <li><strong>Structured Parsing:</strong> Extract todos and JSON from LLM responses</li>
                <li><strong>Server Control:</strong> Start/stop Ollama server via systemctl or Docker</li>
                <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Try::Tiny exception handling with comprehensive diagnostics</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GETTING STARTED SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="getting-started" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Getting Started</h2>
            
            <h3 id="gs-step1" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.1 Basic Usage in a Catalyst Controller</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">To use the Ollama model in your Catalyst application:</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# In a Catalyst Controller
sub ai_query :Local {
    my ($self, $c) = @_;
    
    my $ollama = $c->model('Ollama');
    
    my $response = $ollama->query(
        prompt => "List 3 important tasks for today",
        format => 'json'
    );
    
    my $todos = $ollama->parse_todos($response);
    $c->stash(todos => $todos);
}
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="gs-step2" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.2 Direct Instantiation (Testing)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">For testing or direct usage outside Catalyst:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Direct instantiation
use Comserv::Model::Ollama;

# Local Ollama instance (default localhost:11434)
my $ollama = Comserv::Model::Ollama->new(
    host => 'localhost',
    model => 'llama3.1',
    timeout => 120
);

# Remote Ollama server
my $ollama_remote = Comserv::Model::Ollama->new(
    host => '192.168.1.199',
    model => 'mistral',
    timeout => 120
);

# Or specify endpoint directly (legacy)
my $ollama_legacy = Comserv::Model::Ollama->new(
    endpoint => 'http://192.168.1.199:11434/api/generate',
    model => 'llama3.1',
    timeout => 120
);
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="gs-step3" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.3 Connection Verification</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Always verify Ollama connection before making requests:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
my $connection_status = $ollama->check_connection();
if ($connection_status->{success}) {
    print "Connected to Ollama at: " . $connection_status->{endpoint};
} else {
    print "Connection failed: " . $connection_status->{error};
}
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- METHODS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="methods" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. API Methods</h2>
            
            <h3 id="m-query" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.1 query(%args)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Single-turn query to Ollama model</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>`prompt` - Query text to send to model (required)</li>
                <li>`format` - Response format: 'text' (default) or 'json'</li>
                <li>`stream` - Boolean: enable response streaming (default: 1)</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> String containing model response</p>

            <h3 id="m-chat" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.2 chat(messages => [@messages], %args)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Multi-turn conversation with Ollama model</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>`messages` - Array of message hashes with 'role' (system/user/assistant) and 'content' (required)</li>
                <li>`format` - Response format: 'text' or 'json'</li>
                <li>`stream` - Boolean: enable response streaming</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Model response with streaming support for multi-line output</p>

            <h3 id="m-parse-todos" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.3 parse_todos($response)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Extract todo list items from LLM response</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Array of parsed todo items from markdown or JSON format</p>

            <h3 id="m-list-models" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.4 list_models()</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> List all locally available models on Ollama server</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Array of model names and details</p>

            <h3 id="m-pull-model" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.5 pull_model($model_name)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Download and install a model from Ollama registry</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Parameters:</strong> `$model_name` - Name of model (e.g., 'llama3.1', 'mistral')</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Status hash with success/error</p>

            <h3 id="m-remove-model" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.6 remove_model($model_name)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Delete a locally installed model</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Status hash with success/error</p>

            <h3 id="m-check-connection" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.7 check_connection()</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify connectivity to Ollama server</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Status hash with 'success', 'endpoint', and optional 'error'</p>

            <h3 id="m-start-server" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.8 start_server()</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Start Ollama server (via systemctl or command)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Returns:</strong> Status hash with success/error</p>

            <h3 id="m-set-host" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.9 set_host($host)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Change Ollama host at runtime</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Parameters:</strong> `$host` - Hostname or IP address</p>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ADVANCED USAGE SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="advanced" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Advanced Usage</h2>
            
            <h3 id="adv-streaming" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">6.1 Streaming Responses</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The Ollama model supports streaming responses for real-time output. Streaming is enabled by default:</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Streaming is enabled by default
my $response = $ollama->query(
    prompt => "Write a poem",
    stream => 1
);

# Disable streaming for batch processing
my $response = $ollama->query(
    prompt => "What is 2+2?",
    stream => 0
);
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="adv-json-format" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">6.2 JSON Format Requests</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Request structured JSON responses for programmatic processing:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
my $response = $ollama->query(
    prompt => "Extract the main topic. Format as JSON: {topic: string}",
    format => 'json'
);

# Parse JSON response
my $json_data = JSON::decode_json($response);
print "Topic: " . $json_data->{topic};
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="adv-multi-turn" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">6.3 Multi-Turn Conversations</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Build context-aware conversations with message history:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
my @messages = (
    {role => 'system', content => 'You are a helpful assistant'},
    {role => 'user', content => 'What is machine learning?'},
    {role => 'assistant', content => 'ML is a subset of AI...'},
    {role => 'user', content => 'Give me a concrete example'}
);

my $response = $ollama->chat(messages => \@messages);
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="adv-error-handling" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">6.4 Error Handling</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The Ollama model uses Try::Tiny for robust error handling:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
use Try::Tiny;

try {
    my $response = $ollama->query(prompt => "Hello");
} catch {
    warn "Ollama error: $_";
};
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="adv-remote-server" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">6.5 Remote Server Management</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Switch between local and remote Ollama servers dynamically:</p>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Use local server
$ollama->set_host('localhost');

# Switch to remote server
$ollama->set_host('192.168.1.199');

# Verify connection
my $status = $ollama->get_connection_info();
print "Connected to: " . $status->{endpoint};
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="troubleshooting" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-connection-failed" style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Connection Failed to Ollama Server</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Error messages like "Connection refused", "Timeout", or "Cannot connect to endpoint"</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Verify Ollama server is running: `curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags`</li>
                    <li>Check correct host and port configuration in Ollama instance</li>
                    <li>For remote servers, verify network connectivity: `ping 192.168.1.199`</li>
                    <li>Check firewall rules allow port 11434 access</li>
                    <li>If using Docker, ensure container is running and port is exposed</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-no-models" style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: No Models Available</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> `list_models()` returns empty list or "No models installed"</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Pull a model: `$ollama->pull_model('llama3.1')`</li>
                    <li>Or from command line: `ollama pull llama3.1`</li>
                    <li>List available models on Ollama registry: https://ollama.ai/library</li>
                    <li>Verify model storage has sufficient disk space</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-timeout" style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Request Timeout</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Requests take too long or timeout after specified duration</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Increase timeout parameter: `my $ollama = Comserv::Model::Ollama->new(timeout => 300);`</li>
                    <li>For large models, increase default timeout from 120s to 300s or more</li>
                    <li>Verify Ollama server performance is adequate</li>
                    <li>Consider using a faster model for time-sensitive operations</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-json-parsing" style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: JSON Parsing Fails</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> `JSON::decode_json()` fails or returns unexpected data</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Verify model actually supports JSON format output</li>
                    <li>Include JSON instruction in prompt: "Format as valid JSON: ..."</li>
                    <li>Use `parse_todos()` helper method for structured parsing</li>
                    <li>Check response is valid JSON before parsing: `try { ... } catch { ... }`</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONFIGURATION REFERENCE SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="config-ref" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8. Configuration Reference</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Constructor Attributes</h3>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <th style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Attribute</th>
                    <th style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Type</th>
                    <th style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Default</th>
                    <th style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px; text-align: left;">Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>host</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">String</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">'localhost'</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Ollama server hostname or IP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>port</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Integer</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">11434</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Ollama API port</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>endpoint</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">String</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Auto-built</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Complete API endpoint (auto-built from host:port if not specified)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>model</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">String</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Optional</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Default model name for queries</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>timeout</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Integer</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">120</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Request timeout in seconds</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;"><code>ua</code></td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">LWP::UserAgent</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">Auto-built</td>
                    <td style="border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 8px;">HTTP user agent (auto-created if not provided)</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

